== Description ==

{{Blurimage|width=360px|file=Level-6-A.webp|caption=An image of Level 630.}}
Level 630 is a vast, polluted, adulterated orange forest; estimated to extend 60 million mi².The level includes dull trees, being somewhat damaged and plagued with [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection]], which spans from 10 to 50 feet high; the type of the trees that are present here are oak, birch and other undiscovered types of trees. Other plant life is present on Level 630, such as tangerine shrubs, bushes and grass; often withered and covered in [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection.]] 
{{Blurimage|width=360px|file=Level-6-B.jpg|caption=Another image of Level 630.}}
Aside from plants, other natural objects are also present, including rocks, radioactive rivers, fallen trees and intoxicated lakes. Unique lakes, rivers and ponds are found throughout the level, containing green radioactive water. The water is extremely dangerous and radioactive, as they can dissolve one’s body within seconds and release a thick green smog which may lead to severe health complications and infections when inhaled.  Due to substantial amounts of radiation present within '''Level 630''', visiting the level without any protective gear that does not reduce radiation exposure will likely lead to acute radiation poisoning almost immediately upon entering. 

Abandoned man-made structures covered by [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection]] are also present, which includes cabins, watchtowers, tunnels, piles of logs, and bases; which contains several objects such as tools, almond water, food and other items though they are unusable due to them being broken and covered by [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection.]] These man-made indicates former human habitation before Entity N-5 arrived.

As one wanders far enough in Level 630, one may find an green, motionless ocean made of [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection]] in Level 630. It is not recommended for one to go to the ocean as it contains highly corrosive and radioactive water which is extremely toxic to wanderers. Luckily, the ocean is devoid of harmful entities and include an exit to [[Level 87]] when one travels far enough, though attempts of reaching [[Level 87]] has failed due to the nature of the ocean.

An infamous property of '''Level 630''' that should be noted is that the level is capable of infecting other levels. For example, [[Level 22]] has been contaminated by '''Level 630'''. [[M.E.G.]] Is currently trying to find a cure for this infection; however, they are currently struggling to find one. If a cure cannot be discovered within a timely matter, the infection will quickly spread to other levels and devastate all of the Backrooms. In addition, the infection also may spread to [[The Frontrooms]], causing an end-of-the-world scenario.

=== Temperature and Climate ===

Level 630’s temperature is similar to the frontrooms; as the temperature at daytime ranges from 20°C to 30°C, and at nighttime the temperature ranges from 15°C to 20°C.  The day and night cycle of the level takes approximately 24 hours to complete, leading to 12 hours of sunlight and 12 hours of darkness. The weather of this level is mostly clear, however the level includes special weather events, such as acid rain and radioactive fog; making the level even more dangerous.

=== Level 630 Orgins ===

Level 630 is originally was known as a extremely safe and habitable level. It is theorized at one point, the level was broken into 3 similar levels and drifted apart across [[The Void]]. Soon after [[Phenomenon 100|The Split]], the level’s environment was drastically changed due to Entity N-5 entering the level, contiminating the level with [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection.]] These changes did not just affect the landscape but also affected the flora and fauna, changing the nature of the area altogether. The area underwent severe mutations and expansions, taking on a completely new form from the initial level, no longer bearing any resemblance to its original state. The aftermath made the level one of the most dangerous and uninhabitable levels, due to numerous extremely dangerous environmental hazards and entities.

=== Note ===

A note was found at one of the abandoned outposts before the contamination of Level 630. The writer is presumed to be dead shortly after. <div class="featurebox" style="background:linear-gradient(to bottom, #FFFFFF 24px, #266C91 1px);background-size:40px 25px;border-radius: 0px; margin: 1em">
<span style="color: black;"><span style="font-family:Protest Revolution;">My Journal of Level 630.</span></span>

<span style="color: black;"><span style="font-family:Protest Revolution;">Day 1: I entered through the promising glass doors from [[Level 610]]. It is a safe haven for me, resources are abundant and friendly outposts are everywhere</span></span>

<span style="color: black;"><span style="font-family:Protest Revolution;">Day 2: I sensed something was wrong, the split soon happened, breaking pieces of land and sending wanderers to [[The Void]]. I was lucky enough to survive.</span></span>

<span style="color: black;"><span style="font-family:Protest Revolution;">Day 3: A strange entity called Entity N-5 arrived here, polluting most of the landscape. The level i thought to be home has transformed into a hazardous wasteland.</span></span>

<span style="color: black;"><span style="font-family:Protest Revolution;">Day 4: The level is no longer habitable, most of the outposts evacuated, and nuclear entities began appearing, killing most wanderers.</span></span> 
</div>
==Entities==
Although '''Level 630''' was once devoid of harmful entities, many hostilities entered from [[The Hive]] and [[Level 870]], which soon became mutated by [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection]].
<tabber>
|-|Nuclear Membri=
=Nuclear Membri=
==Description==

{{Blurimage|file=Aranea Membri Variant.png|hovertext=Nuclear Membri|caption=An image of the '''Nuclear Membri''' charging at a wanderer. The photographer was presumed dead.}} 

The '''Nuclear Membri''', also known as Entity N-1 (Nuclear-1), was the first entity to be discovered in '''Level 630'''. It is a variant of the [[Entity 62|Aranea Membri]]. Compared to its [[Entity 62|original version]], '''Nuclear Membri''' specimens are greener in appearance with neon red eyes.
==Biology==
'''Nuclear Membri''' possess three legs and half of their cracked skulls are exposed. Not much is known about the biology of '''Nuclear Membri''' as their internals undergo rapid solvation upon the cessation of brain activity. 
==Behaviour==
'''Nuclear Membri''' can sniff out their prey from 27-34m (90-110ft) away. Similar to its original version and can reach up to 50 mph (80 kph). As a result of the layout in '''Level 630''', it is nearly impossible to outrun them.

Unlike its original version, it does not catch its prey by emerging from the ceiling. Instead, it will burrow underground until it sniffs out its prey; once it sniffs out its target, it will burrow up and chase its prey.

|-|Skin-Dissolvers=
=Skin-Dissolvers=
==Description==
'''Skin-Dissolvers''', also known as Entity N-2, are variants of [[Entity 10|Skin-Stealers]]. Despite having the same body as a [[Entity 10|Skin-Stealer]], they are green in color and appear to be more deformed than a regular [[Entity 10|Skin-Stealer]].
==Biology==
'''Skin-Dissolvers''' have an identical appearance to [[Entity 10|Skin-Stealers]], except '''Skin-Dissolvers''' are tinted green, and have swollen eyes, along with many of their organs exposed.
==Behaviour==
'''Skin-Disolvers''' feast on Corrosive Moths, but humans are their primary prey. However, they do not eat human skin as it is poisonous to them. As a result of the deadly skin, they spit out a corrosive substance contained in their stomach to burn their victim’s skin. If this substance is left within their stomach for too long, it will eventually dissolve their body, killing them. As a result, they puncture their stomach to drain the fluid twice a month and the damage will quickly heal.
[[File:Skin-DissolverScream.mp3|thumb|The screams of a '''Skin-Dissolver'''.]]
Unlike their original counterpart, '''Skin-Dissolvers''' are typically aggressive, since they need to consume large amounts of food to survive. Most of their food becomes the corrosive substance that breaks down human skin, and they seem to have an extremely powerful instinct to obtain as much of the substance as possible. When a '''Skin-Dissolver''' has no corrosive substance contained in their stomach, they will become passive. While passive, they will not attack any humans and will switch to hunting Corrosive Moths. It is believed that this happens because human skin is poisonous to '''Skin-Dissolvers''', and without any corrosive substance to destroy human skin, they can no longer eat them.
|-|Corrosive Moths=
=Corrosive Moths=
==Description==
'''Corrosive Moths''', also known as Entity N-3, are similar to [[Entity 4|Deathmoths]], but are rather tinted green. In addition to similarities, they are also more passive than [[Entity 4|Deathmoths]], but will be damaging when provoked; when a '''Corrosive Moth''' is hurt, it will bleed out corrosive liquid, which can burn one’s flesh within seconds. '''Corrosive Moths''' have several predators, including Skin-Dissolvers, Nuclear Membris, Deathfishes, and more.
==Biology==
As stated above, they are similar to [[Entity 4|Deathmoths]] but are tinted green. In addition, they are unable to produce [[Object 6|Moth Jelly]] but instead will produce [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection]].
==Behaviour==
'''Corrosive Moths''' are attracted to light, similar to moths from [[the Frontrooms]]. '''Corrosive Moths''' weakest sense is sight as they have blurry vision. Although their vision is bad, '''Corrosive Moths''' have an excellent sense of smell, which is used to detect food and nearby predators. It is unknown what '''Corrosive Moths''' feed on, but it is theorized that they eat the contaminated grass found frequently in '''Level 630'''. Despite their aggressive original variants and the environment they live in, '''Corrosive Moths''' are passive. In fact, 'it is the only entity in Level 630 that isn't hostile.

|-|Deathfishes=
=Deathfishes=
==Description==

{{Blurimage|file=Deathfish.jpg|hovertext=Deathfish|caption=A photograph of a Deathfish that recently died.}}

'''Deathfishes''', designated as Entity N-4, are green starfishes that can travel on land for at least a few hours. Their arms have suction cups, similar to a starfish in [[The Frontrooms]]. '''Deathfishes''' is 1 of the 2 entities on '''Level 630''' that isn't a variant of another entity.

'''Deathfish''' are extremely dangerous, and should be avoided at all costs. If a '''Deathfish''' touches a person with its arms, it will rip off their skin with its suction cups, and proceed to inject a toxic slew of poisons into their victim’s body. Once their victim is dead (which normally takes about thirty seconds), they will begin feeding on their corpse.
==Biology==
'''Deathfishes''' are green starfish that can vary in different sizes, with some being 4 cm wide and 3 cm tall, while others being as big as 34 feet wide and 31 feet tall. However, the bigger it is, the easier it is to run away from this entity. 
==Behaviour==
'''Deathfishes''' are mainly aggressive towards all life on '''Level 630''', but mainly attack humans as their primary feeding. '''Deathfishes''' tend to hide from their prey so they don't notice them. However, once the prey comes near them, they will quickly jump on them and begin attacking them.
|-|The Nucleigo=
=The Nucleigo=
==Description==

{{Blurimage|file=Nucleigo .jpg|hovertexk=The Nucleigo|caption=Artists drawing of the Nucleigo based off of surviving victims reports.}} 

Entity N-5, also known as “The Nucleigo" or "The Destroyer of Levels", is a 22ft (6.7m) wendigo-like entity that produces [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection]], moreover, the Nucleigo is the primary reason why '''Level 630''' has turned into a polluted wasteland. Under no circumstances should anyone come near Entity N-5, as it will mean certain death. This beast can run approximately 120mph (200kph) and will devour any victims it sees. Entity N-5 did not originate from '''Level 630''', as it arrived from another level; many suggest that level being [[Level 870]]. 

Huge skeletal parts that may match Entity N-5 have been discovered in other levels, such as [[Level 998]]; this may indicate that there were other Nucleigos, but they all went extinct except for one, that being the one that inhabits '''Level 630'''.
==Biology==
The actual physical description of Entity N-5 is unknown due to being nearly extinct and incredibly difficult to find. However, the following details of Entity N-5 are based on victims who survived this entity: Entity N-5 takes the appearance of a 22ft wendigo with a giant hole on its back; an infinite production of [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection]] appears to be dripping down from this hole. 
==Behaviour==
Entity N-5 has no remorse for what it kills, as it is hostile to all entities and wanderers, and it will give the most gruesome death to its victims. These include: trampling the bodies of their victims, tearing their victims' bodies one by one, and even going as far as forcing them to eat their body parts.
</tabber>

== Colonies and Outposts ==
Due to the nature of this level, it is impossible to create outposts here.

== Entrances and Exits ==
=== Entrances ===
*Rarely, one may enter this level by finding and walking toward an extremely rare passage from [[Level 626]].
* Getting -150 karma or lower in [[Level 995]] will send one here.
*Entering a glass door on [[Level 610]] with the inscription "630" above the door will lead you here.
*Using an elevator on [[Level 22]] that leads to levels instead of floors and selecting '''630''' will bring you here.
===Exits===
*Finding a rare underground entrance will lead one to either [[Level 64]] or [[The Hive]].
*Travelling far enough in the oceans will take one to [[Level 87]].
*[[Noclipping]] into a freestanding grey pillar will bring you to [[Level 610]], however if one noclips in a red pillar, one will be taken to [[Level 850]] instead.
*One may exit by tripping and noclipping on a lake, leading to [[Level 870]], however this is incredibly hard to do.
*Passing out in the level’s ocean may lead to [[Level 351]].

==Addendum==
