<center> {{Collapse|num=420|initial=<span style="font-size: 24px;">Open contamination of Level 630</span>|final=<span style="font-size: 24px;">Close contamination of Level 630</span>|body=''The following information, while some of it is verified fact, is a likely timeline for what happened in '''Level 630''', based off of testimony from former settlers within the level and M.E.G. experiments and simulations.''


'''2014/8/10 1:00 PM LT (1 day before Entity N-5 arrival)''' On 2014/8/10, [[Phenomenon 100|The Split]] occurred, breaking the level into 2 pieces, which eventually became [[Level 626]] and [[Level 630]]. While the levels drifted along the void, various entities soon entered the level from [[The Hive]] and [[Level 870]]; due to various anomalies.

'''2014/8/11 1:00 PM LT (0 hours after Entity N-5 arrival)''' On 2014/8/11, an entity known as the "Nucleigo" arrived in '''Level 630'''. It is unknown where it came from, but many speculate that the entity came from [[Level 870]]. Upon arrival, it began to release [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection]] from its body, which contaminated large portions of [[Object 1|Almond Water]].

'''2014/8/11 3:00 PM LT (2 hours after Entity N-5 arrival)''' Plants within '''Level 630''' began losing their color and wilting. A couple of wanderers, seeing what was happening, fled the level. Most were unaware of what was happening or did not think it was an issue.

'''2014/8/11 4:00 PM LT (3 hours after Entity N-5 arrival)''' The clouds started turning a light shade of green.

'''2014/8/11 5:00 PM LT (4 hours after Entity N-5 arrival)''' Plants began to wilt and become a light shade of orange. The Tree Residents held an emergency meeting, and it was decided to evacuate via a nearby exit to [[Level 87]].

'''2014/8/11 6:00 PM LT (5 hours after Entity N-5 arrival)''' Plants started withering and turning a dull shade of orange, and the clouds fully transitioned to a shade of green. By this time, the Tree Residents fully evacuated.

'''2014/8/11 7:00 PM LT (6 hours after Entity N-5 arrival)''' By this time, Entity N-5 had saturated most of the [[Object 1|Almond Water]] lakes, rivers, and oceans within ten miles of the Nucleigo’s entrance point, turning them into a cocktail of [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection]].

'''2014/8/11 8:00 PM LT (7 hours after Entity N-5 arrival)''' The changes to '''Level 630''' became more and more obvious.

Over the next 12 hours, the area affected by the [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection]] continued to expand, reaching 100 miles from Entity N-5’s entrance point by 4:00 AM LT on August 12. Most of the plants within that area had withered and had become a dull orange. The majority of the trees had been destroyed.

'''2014/8/12 10:00 AM LT (21 hours after Entity N-5 arrival)''' All tree houses constructed by the Tree Residents were destroyed, due to the trees they were on falling or the wood rotting.

At about this time, Outpost 630 became aware of what was happening. They immediately began to evacuate, heading for the exit to the exit the Tree Residents had used earlier. Unfortunately, a combination of the now-corrupted environment and the bloodthirsty Entity N-5 caused over half of them to die before they reached the exit.

'''2014/8/12 12:00 PM LT (23 hours after Entity N-5 arrival)''' The atmosphere of '''Level 630''' became hazardous, due to the fog produced by [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection]].

'''2014/8/12 1:00 PM LT (1 day after Entity N-5 arrival)'''All previously-explored areas of '''Level 630''' became fully contaminated.

'''2014/8/13 (2 days after Entity N-5 arrival)''' Almost all wanderers who did not manage to escape '''Level 630'''died.

'''2014/8/14 (3 days after Entity N-5 arrival)''' The [[M.E.G.]]<nowiki/>learns of what happened in '''Level 630'''. Immediately, they and the Forest Backrooms Alliance begin dispatching aid to the survivors in Level 87 and elsewhere possible and begin the process of debriefing survivors.

'''2014/8/18 (7 days after Entity N-5 arrival)''' During an M.E.G. exploration mission in '''Level 630''', a Nuclear Membri is found. Before it attacked the team, it was killed by a harpoon. In addition, a remotely-operated drone was sent into a cave entrance; the drone stumbled upon [[The Hive]], explaining why entities started randomly appearing in '''Level 630'''.

'''2018/2/14 (Several years after Entity N-5 arrival)''' A newly discovered level––later assigned to [[Level 64]]––was revealed to have strong resemblances to '''Level 630'''. The M.E.G. deploys a team to investigate. Several litres of [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection]] are discovered. This leads to a theory that '''Level 630''' is infecting other levels with [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection]], which is confirmed a few weeks later when huge portions of [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection]] are found in [[Level 22]]. 

If [[Object 3|Nuclear Infection]] keeps spreading towards other levels, there is a chance that some of the substance could enter [[The Frontrooms]], leading to a hypothetical end-of-the-world scenario.}} </center>

